<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="826" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d826">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12560.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of War</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">War Department</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 18, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Secretary of War presents his compliments to the Honorable the
                            Secretary of State and quotes, for his information, the following
                            telegram from the Commanding General at Vera Cruz, dated July 17, 1914:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Huerta, Blanquet and party reached Puerto Mexico 8.15 this
                                    evening.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>